-- Ukraine ceasefire news boosts Raiffeisen shares
-- By Michael Shields
-- Wed Sep 03, 2014 04:54AM EDT
-- None



VIENNA, Sept 3 (Reuters) - Shares in Austrian lender Raiffeisen Bank International <RBIV.VI>, emerging Europe's second-biggest lender, rose nearly 9 percent on Wednesday after Ukraine's president said he had reached a ceasefire deal with Russia for eastern Ukraine's Donbass region. [ID:nL5N0R41GF]

RBI is the European bank most exposed to business in Russia and relies heavily on that market for profits.